CUSTOM AMI :

  DATA
  PACKAGE 
  SERVICES /APPLICATION 


    WHAT IS AN AMI IN AWS?

    --------------------------------------------------
    OVERVIEW
    --------------------------------------------------

        AMI stands for Amazon Machine Image.
        It is a pre-configured template used to launch
  

        An AMI contains:
            • Operating system (Linux/Windows)
            • Pre-installed software
            • Settings and configurations
            • EBS snapshot of the root volume

        Launching an EC2 = Using an AMI as the blueprint.


    --------------------------------------------------
    TYPES OF AMIs
    --------------------------------------------------

        1) AWS-provided AMIs
            - Amazon Linux, Ubuntu, Windows, RedHat

        2) Marketplace AMIs
            - Vendor provided (Nginx, Jenkins, Fortinet)

        3) Custom AMIs (created by you)
            - Your own configuration and setup


    --------------------------------------------------
    WHY DO WE NEED CUSTOM AMIs?
    --------------------------------------------------

        Custom AMIs are required when you want *your own*
        pre-configured server template.

        Reasons to create a custom AMI:

        1) Faster Launch Times
            - Example:
                You install Java, Tomcat, Python, app code.
                Taking a snapshot → creates an AMI.
                Now launching new EC2 takes seconds.

        2) Standardization
            - Every server launched from this AMI
              has the same OS, packages, versions.

        3) Disaster Recovery
            - If an instance crashes,
              launch a new instance from the AMI.

        4) Auto Scaling Groups
            - ASGs require custom AMIs for apps.
            - They rapidly create new instances during traffic spikes.

        5) Pre-configured Security Hardening
            - OS patches, firewall rules, packages already applied.

        6) Golden Image Pattern (Industry Standard)
            - Companies maintain a “Golden AMI”
            - This is the official, secure, prebuilt server image.


    --------------------------------------------------
    REAL DEVOPS USE CASES
    --------------------------------------------------

        • Auto Scaling launch templates
        • Preinstalled Jenkins/Java/Nginx/httpd on EC2
        • Baking application code into the AMI (Packer)
        • Creating golden images for production
        • Backup of critical servers


    --------------------------------------------------
    INTERVIEW ONE-LINER
    --------------------------------------------------

        AMI is a machine template used to launch EC2 instances.
        Custom AMIs allow us to pre-install software, apply
        configurations, and create standardized, fast, and
        production-ready server deployments.


